examples.en: I was stationed overseas at the time.
The troops were stationed near London.
A security guard was stationed near the door.
American troops were stationed on Japanese soil.
He stationed himself by the door to greet the guests.
Over 10,000 military personnel were stationed in the country.
The police stationed sharpshooters on rooftops all along the route of the presidential motorcade.
She was plagued with an unquiet mind the whole time her son was stationed overseas.
